<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-12-06T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-12-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="747" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d747">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">394.1153 Smith Company, Werner G./77:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-06T17:00:00-05:00">December 6, 1938—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>640. Your 1423, November 18, 7 p.m., wood oil. Werner G. Smith authorizes
                            acceptance of Japanese offer to pay for the remaining part of the
                            shipment consisting of approximately 120 short tons without any further
                            effort to obtain payment for the entire original shipment, and expresses
                            the wish that settlement be made accordingly.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Chungking and Hankow.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>